<h3>ENIAC and Univac: The Computer is Born</h3>

** 1900-late 1940's: electrical programmable calculating machines:
       Zuse Z2-Z3, Harvard/IBM Mark I (1944), ENIAC, Colossus; 1945: Von
       Neumann stored-program computer model; 1947: transistor (Bardeen,
       Brattain, Shockley); 1948: Manchester Mark I, first
       stored-program digital computer
** PEOPLE: Eckert, Mauchly, Atanasoff, Von Neumann
** ANECDOTES: Eckert/Mauchly, U Penn patent disputes; Von Neumann political
stuff

