<td>The first company in what would become Silicon Valley.  Fairchild
Semiconductor is all but defunct??, but [list of companies] can trace
their genealogy directly to Fairchild.
</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><b>Meanwhile, Back On the Farm</b></td>
<td>1952: Adm. Grace Murray Hopper develops A-0, the first
<i>compiler</i> that translates English-like programming languages to
computers' native machine language.</td></tr>
